1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the concept of cognitive radio and its evolution towards intelligent communication, which is closely related to networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper highlights the recent achievements in AI-enabled intelligent radio, indicating a strong connection to the field of artificial intelligence. 
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses spectrum sensing and sharing, which is related to information theory and communication systems. 
4. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper may touch upon security issues related to cognitive and intelligent radio. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper may discuss the challenges and solutions related to the control and optimization of wireless devices in intelligent communication systems.
